\section{Echo Physics}

For $\beta>\beta_c$, no horizon exists. The inner boundary condition is therefore no longer purely absorbing and may become reflective or partially reflective, as in other horizonless compact-object scenarios \cite{Cardoso2016,Cardoso2019}.

The echo delay is approximately
\begin{equation}
\Delta t_{\mathrm{echo}}
\simeq
2
\int_{r_0}^{r_{\mathrm{ph}}}
\frac{dr}{F(r)}.
\end{equation}

Near the critical regime,
\begin{equation}
\Delta t_{\mathrm{echo}}
\to
\infty
\quad
\text{as}
\quad
\beta\to\beta_c^{+}.
\end{equation}

